<WorkshopLayout title="Welcome" description="Get up to speed with Cursor and GitHub.">
  <h1>Welcome to the Cursor Workshop</h1>
  <p>
    This workshop helps you get started with <strong>Cursor</strong> and <strong>GitHub</strong>. By the end, you’ll have cloned this repo, opened it in Cursor, run it on your computer, and explored the basics of both tools.
  </p>

  <h2>What you’ll learn</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>What GitHub is and why we use it</li>
    <li>How to clone a repo and run it locally</li>
    <li>How to find your way around Cursor (sidebar, command palette, chat)</li>
    <li>A simple checklist so you can track your progress</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What you need</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cursor</strong> – <a href="https://cursor.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download Cursor</a> if you haven’t already.</li>
    <li><strong>GitHub account</strong> – You’ll create one in the next section if you don’t have it yet.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Ready? Start with <a href="/cursor-workshop/github/">GitHub basics</a>, then follow <a href="/cursor-workshop/clone-and-run/">Clone and run</a> to get this workshop running on your machine.
  </p>
</WorkshopLayout>
